title: RainToday vs Cloud3pm
body: Based on the visualization of the feature RainToday and Coud3pm, it is seen that there will be no rain tomorrow even if the cloud obscured is the range of 5.33 - 8.

title: Sunshine
body: There is uneven error distribution for the feature sunshine in order to predict rain for tomorrow.

title: Humidity3pm vs MaxTemp
body: Based on the Humidity3pm vs MaxTemp, it is interesting to see that it is very unlikely for the rain to occur tomorrow if the humidity was very high and the temp was max too. For lower temper with high humidity the prediction of rain to happen is more than the former condition.

title: Humidity vs WindGustSpeed
body: It is found that when the WindGUstSpeed is greater than or equal 48 and the Humidity3pm is greater than or equal to 66.67 its most likely to rain tomorrow.

title: Current_Day_Rainfall
body: It is interesting to see that it would not be right to say that it will likely rain tomorrow based on today's rainfall. The higher the amount of rain, the lower is the prediction rate.
